   <sec>
    <sec>
     <sec>
      <p>
      </p>
      <title>
       Materials and Plasmids
      </title>
      <p>
       Ferric-dicitrate was made by mixing a 2-fold excess of citric acid with ferrous ammonium sulfate in water. During neutralization with NaOH, iron oxidizes, and the solution turns green-brown. Plasmid pGSO164 containing the entire
       <em>
        suf
       </em>
       operon from
       <em>
        E. coli
       </em>
       was used to express and purify the SufBCD complex (
       <xref ref-type="bibr">
        14
       </xref>
       ). Plasmids pET-Shis, pET-Ehis encoding the His-tagged SufS and SufE, as well as pET3aSufB, pET3aSufC, and pET3aSufD encoding SufB, SufC, and SufD proteins were obtained as described previously (
       <xref ref-type="bibr">
        13
       </xref>
       ,
       <xref ref-type="bibr">
        19
       </xref>
       ,
       <xref ref-type="bibr">
        26
       </xref>
       ). Plasmid pG5783 encoding aconitase B was a gift from J. R. Guest (Norwich, UK).
